{
  "texts": [
    "Despite taxonomic anchoring, performance varies by entity type-well-defined categories like Teleconnection achieve 0.61 F1 versus 0.04 F1 for ambiguous Platform entities.",
    "Acronym disambiguation (e.g., \"SAM\" vs. \"Southern Annular Mode\") remains unresolved, with 58% of errors stemming from partial term extraction.",
    "The entity linking process presents technical challenges, particularly in our fuzzy string matching approach for Wikidata integration.",
    "Using a 60% similarity threshold involves trade-offs between coverage and accuracy, potentially missing valid matches or creating incorrect associations for complex scientific terms.",
    "Our method's focus on English-language scientific literature introduces a language bias, potentially overlooking valuable climate knowledge in other languages."
  ]
}